<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Never use the PTO gear as a pressing base. The narrow width of this gear can cause breakage.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear retaining snap ring from each countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301788">Figure 88</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301788" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301788" filename="../figg13/G1301788.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 88. Drive Gear Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the rear face of 3rd speed gear as a base, press the drive gear, PTO gear, and 3rd
                speed gear from each countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301789">Figure 89</hotlnk>). This also removes the front bearing inner race.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301789" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301789" filename="../figg13/G1301789.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 89. Drive Gear, PTO Gear and 3rd Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the key and roll pin; replace if necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301790">Figure 90</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301790" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301790" filename="../figg13/G1301790.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 90. Inspect Key and Roll Pin</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
